===Etymology===

ipu > iɸu > *iwu > iu. Medial /h/ regularly changed from [p] > [ɸ] > [w]. Japanese never distinguished between /wu/ and /u/, so in it automatically becomes [u]. The /w/ only surfaces in negative form: iwanai, where the phoneme /wa/ exists. Surface forms /iwimasu/ and /iwemasu/ automatically become [iimasu] and [iemasu] since Japanese no longer has phonemes for /wi, we/. Possibly related to Korean [[입|ip]] "mouth".

